1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Your brain has a limit—overload it, and you forget everything.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,000
This is Cognitive Load Theory.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,200
It explains how our working memory handles information.

4
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:10,400
Too much info?

5
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,800
Your brain might just shut down.

6
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:16,000
Imagine trying to learn when your mind's overwhelmed.

7
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Research shows optimal learning happens when cognitive load is balanced.

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,600
Less is often more.

9
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:25,200
By minimizing distractions and focusing, you can boost retention.

10
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,200
Your brain will thank you.

11
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:31,200
Want to learn more about how to optimize your learning?

